<m0>(box) COLOMBIA <m0>(--) A congressional panel finished its investigation Thursday into allegations that President Ernesto Samper financed his 1994 campaign with drug money. It has 10 days to make a recommendation to Congress about claims that Samper solicited $6 million in contributions from the Cali Cartel.<ql>
<m0>(box) CUBA <m0>(--) An anti-cholera vaccine developed through genetic engineering is being tested on humans, said Gustavo Sierra, head of Cuba's Program of Vaccine and Research and Development.<ql>
<m0>(box) HONDURAS <m0>(--) Foreign Minister Delmer Urbizo Panting said Thursday that a meeting of the commission studying Honduras-El Salvador border problems ended without achieving progress on the issues. <ql>
